parameters.textBody: Let's do it! What's your full name?

=Your Angel Canvas will take around 10–15 minutes to complete. 

Would you like to start now, or should I send you a reminder for later?

1. Start now
2. Remind me tomorrow
3. Remind me in 2 days

=*Alright {{ $('Chat start').item.json.contacts[0].profile.name.split(" ")[0] }}, let's customize your canvas.*

(1/21) What's your previous experience investing in startups?

(If multiple, enter your answers separated by a space e.g. A B C)

A. I've never invested in startups
B. I invested through crowdfunding or VC funds
C. I invested as solo angel
D. I invested through an investment vehicle with few people
E. I invested through an angel syndicate
F. I invested through an angel fund
G. I've been an angel for 1 to 3 years
H. I've been an angel for 3 to 5 years
I. I've been an angel for 5 to 10 years
J. I've been an angel for more than 10 years

=(2/21) How do you perceive your role as an angel investor?

A. As a hobby – I invest primarily for enjoyment and personal interest.
B. As a remunerated job – I see it as a professional activity with financial returns.
C. As an entrepreneurial career – I approach it as a long-term business venture.
D. As a calling to contribute – I invest to support entrepreneurs and create impact.

"Angel investing gives me the opportunity for involvement with startups"

"Angel investing allows me to mentor entrepreneurs"

=(8/21) What future changes in the world do you foresee and would love to be part of?

(If multiple, enter your answers separated by a space e.g. A B C)

A. AI (Artificial Intelligence)
B. Longevity & Health
C. Space & Interplanetary Life
D. New Energy Sources
E. Decentralized Finance & Power
F. Green Revolution & Sustainability
G. Future of Work
H. Consumer Tech and E-commerce
I. Personalized Learning & Human Potential
J. A More Inclusive & Equal World
K. A More Meritocratic & Productive World
L. Not sure
M. Other

=(9/21) Which are the main challenges in the world that startups can solve?

(If multiple, enter your answers separated by a space e.g. A B C)

A. Climate & Sustainability
B. Healthcare & Well-being
C. Financial Innovation
D. Education & Future of Work
E. Food & Agriculture
F. Urbanization & Mobility
G. Cybersecurity & Privacy
H. Aging & Accessibility
I. Democracy & Human Rights
J. Space & Exploration
K. Defense & Security
L. Leisure & Lifestyle
M. Big Data & Productivity
N. Spirituality & Self-Growth
O. Not sure
P. Other

=(10/21) How much time do you want to dedicate to angel investing?

A. Hands-On Partner (20 plus hours per week)
B. Engaged Investor (10 to 20 hours per week)
C. Active Part Time (5 to 10 hours per week)
D. Advisor and Mentor (2 to 5 hours per week)
E. Part Hands-On (1 hour per week)
F. Regular Check-Ins (30 min per week)
G. As low as possible (1 hour per month)
H. Hands-Off Investor
I. Not sure
J. Other

=(12/21) What do you want founders to say about me? (Pick Max. 5)

(If multiple, enter your answers separated by commas e.g. A, B, C)

A. "You guided us through every challenge with wisdom and support"
B. "You provided us game changing insights and guidance"
C. "Your backing elevated our reputation in the industry"
D. "Thanks to your support, we scaled faster than we ever imagined"
E. "You empowered us to think bigger and move bolder"
F. "You believed in us before anyone else did"
G. "Your connections opened doors we never thought possible"
H. "Having you as an investor gave us the credibility we needed to attract others"
I. "You backed us with capital and trust, letting us build our vision"
J. Not sure
K. Other

=(13/21) What do you want other angels to say about you? (Pick Max. 5)

(If multiple, enter your answers separated by commas e.g. A, B, C)

A. "You spot game-changing opportunities before they go mainstream"
B. "You actively contribute to growing the angel and startup community"
C. "You bride startups with the right people, resources, and investors"
D. "Your track record of successful exits speaks for itself"
E. "You are willing to take calculated risks on groundbreaking ideas"
F. "You provide valuable guidance and support to both founders and fellow investors"
G. "You bring deep insights and data-driven decision-making to the table"
H. "You are known for your fairness, transparency, and long-term commitment"
I. Not sure
J. Other

=(14/21) How much would you be comfortable investing? 

(Strike a balance between making meaningful investments in startups and protecting your financial security)

A. $500K or more in total
B. $250K to $500K in total
C. $100K to $250K in total
D. $50K to $100K in total
E. $20K to $50K in total
F. Less than $20K in total
G. $250K or more per year
H. $100K to $250K per year
I. $50K to $100K per year
J. $20K to 50K per year
K. $10K to $20K per year
L. Not sure
M. Other

=(15/21) How many startups would you like to invest on?

A. 50 plus startups – Super-angel strategy, spreading risk across many ventures
B. 20 to 50 startups – Aggressive diversification
C. 10 to 20 startups – Balanced risk across multiple bets
D. 5 to 10 startups – Focused portfolio with calculated risk
E. 1 to 5 startups – Selective, high-conviction
F. Not sure
G. Other

=(16/21) What types of startups will you invest in? (Pick Max. 3)

(If multiple, enter your answers separated by commas e.g. A, B, C)

A. Idea Stage
B. MVP Stage
C. Early Revenue
D. Series A
E. Post-Series A+
F. Not sure
G. Other

=(17/21) What’s your investment return time frame?

A. I prefer to have smaller returns for my investment but exiting sooner (less than 5 years)
B. I'm looking to maximize the outcome, looking for big returns even if I need to wait (more than 5 years)
C. Not sure
D. Other

=(11/21) What can be your key contributions beyond capital? (Pick Max. 3)

(If multiple, enter your answers separated by commas e.g. A, B, C)

A. Industry Expertise
B. Operational Experience
C. Network & Connections
D. Fundraising Support
E. Crisis Counselor/Trusted Confidant
F. Clients Introductions
G. Go-to-Market Strategy
H. Product Development
I. Hiring & Talent Support
J. Hands-On Advisory
K. Not sure
L. Other

=(18/21) In which geographies will you invest? (Pick Max. 3)

(If multiple, enter your answers separated by commas e.g. A, B, C)

A. Local Market – Startups within a 1 hour reach by car.
B. Regional Market – Startups within a 2 hour reach by car.
C. Continental Market - Startups within a 2 hour reach by plane.
D. Global Approach – Open to investing anywhere in the world.
E. Remote-First Startups – I invest in globally distributed teams.
F. Emerging Markets
G. Top Tier Startup Hubs
H. Other

=(19/21) What types of business models will you back? (Pick Max. 5)

(If multiple, enter your answers separated by commas e.g. A, B, C)

A. I'm agnostic
B. B2B (Business-to-Business)
C. B2C (Business-to-Consumer)
D. DTC (Direct-to-Consumer)
E. SaaS (Service-as-a-Software/Digital Agents)
F. SaaS (Software-as-a-Service)
G. E-Commerce
H. Marketplace Models
I. Tokenized & Web3 Models
J. Not sure
K. Other
=(20/21) What are the key reasons that have kept you from angel investing in the past? (Optional)
